/*Write a program using one print statement to print the
pattern of asterisks as shown below:
*
* *
* * *
* * * *
* * * * *

*/
#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    int i, j;
    for(i = 1; i <= 5; i++) {
        for(j = 1; j <= i; j++) {
            printf("* ");
        }
        printf("\n");
    }
    return 0;
}

/*Explanation:
The outer loop (i) controls the number of rows.
The inner loop (j) prints i asterisks in each row.
printf("* ") prints an asterisk followed by a space for spacing.
printf("\n") moves to the next line after printing a row.*/
